  "lore": {
    "key": "Tbl_Unit_Desc_300",
    "english": "The true form of Snake Lady, the host of the Chaos Arena. Her real identity is a Goddess of Snakes, one of the three chiefs of the Naga clan, also worshipped as 'Kaliya' in India.\n\nA highly dangerous enemy as a mythical demon, she enjoys injecting venom into her victims just by touching them and watching them struggle.\n\nNumerous Taimanins, starting with Captain Igawa Asagi, have battled against her, and an analysis of her abilities in combat based on these battles is databased in Gosha. Nevertheless, it is said that she has never revealed her true powers.",
    "japanese": "The true form of Snake Lady, the host of the Chaos Arena. Her real identity is a Goddess of Snakes, one of the three chiefs of the Naga clan, also worshipped as 'Kaliya' in India.\n\nA highly dangerous enemy as a mythical demon, she enjoys injecting venom into her victims just by touching them and watching them struggle.\n\nNumerous Taimanins, starting with Captain Igawa Asagi, have battled against her, and an analysis of her abilities in combat based on these battles is databased in Gosha. Nevertheless, it is said that she has never revealed her true powers.",
    "korean": "The true form of Snake Lady, the host of the Chaos Arena. Her real identity is a Goddess of Snakes, one of the three chiefs of the Naga clan, also worshipped as 'Kaliya' in India.\n\nA highly dangerous enemy as a mythical demon, she enjoys injecting venom into her victims just by touching them and watching them struggle.\n\nNumerous Taimanins, starting with Captain Igawa Asagi, have battled against her, and an analysis of her abilities in combat based on these battles is databased in Gosha. Nevertheless, it is said that she has never revealed her true powers.",
    "chinese_simplified": "The true form of Snake Lady, the host of the Chaos Arena. Her real identity is a Goddess of Snakes, one of the three chiefs of the Naga clan, also worshipped as 'Kaliya' in India.\n\nA highly dangerous enemy as a mythical demon, she enjoys injecting venom into her victims just by touching them and watching them struggle.\n\nNumerous Taimanins, starting with Captain Igawa Asagi, have battled against her, and an analysis of her abilities in combat based on these battles is databased in Gosha. Nevertheless, it is said that she has never revealed her true powers.",
    "chinese_traditional": "The true form of Snake Lady, the host of the Chaos Arena. Her real identity is a Goddess of Snakes, one of the three chiefs of the Naga clan, also worshipped as 'Kaliya' in India.\n\nA highly dangerous enemy as a mythical demon, she enjoys injecting venom into her victims just by touching them and watching them struggle.\n\nNumerous Taimanins, starting with Captain Igawa Asagi, have battled against her, and an analysis of her abilities in combat based on these battles is databased in Gosha. Nevertheless, it is said that she has never revealed her true powers.",
    "spanish": "The true form of Snake Lady, the host of the Chaos Arena. Her real identity is a Goddess of Snakes, one of the three chiefs of the Naga clan, also worshipped as 'Kaliya' in India.\n\nA highly dangerous enemy as a mythical demon, she enjoys injecting venom into her victims just by touching them and watching them struggle.\n\nNumerous Taimanins, starting with Captain Igawa Asagi, have battled against her, and an analysis of her abilities in combat based on these battles is databased in Gosha. Nevertheless, it is said that she has never revealed her true powers."
  },
